Displaying the head of the dataframe for the results of DESeq2 (gene expression calculation tool). Also the size factors for DESeq2, which scales all of the differential gene expression samples with respect to the medians of medians.

c1<-sum(results$padj<.0001,na.rm = TRUE)

log<-results$pvalue<.05

library("ggplot2")
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.2.2
rn<-rownames(resSort[1:10,])
for (x in rn){
  d<-plotCounts(dds, gene=x, intgroup = "sample",col=factor(c("Healthy","Deprived")),returnData=TRUE)
  Sleep<-rep(c("Healthy","Deprived"),6)
  d<-cbind(d,Sleep)
  print(ggplot(d,aes(d$sample,d$count,col=Sleep))+geom_point()+geom_line(group=Sleep)+scale_y_log10()+ylab("Normalized Gene Count")+xlab("Sample")+ggtitle(x))
}

PCA plot between the 12 samples (6 Healthy, 6 Deprived):

library(ggplot2)
pca<-prcomp(t(fdf))
#plot(pca$x[,1], pca$x[,2])

pcavr<-round(pcav/sum(pcav)*100,2)
pcavr[1:2]
## [1] 96.85  2.23
Sleep<-rep(c("Healthy","Deprived"),6)
pcap<-data.frame(Sample=sample,X=pca$x[,1],Y=pca$x[,2])
ggplot(data=pcap,aes(x=X,y=Y,label=Sample,col=Sleep))+geom_point()+geom_text(hjust=.4, vjust=-.5,size=3,colour=rep(c(4,2),times=6))+xlab(paste("PC1 - ",pcavr[1],"%"))+ylab(paste("PC2 - ",pcavr[2],"%"))

The first principal component accounts for more than 98% of the variance between the healthy and deprived samples

The Heatmap shows significant clustering between healthy and deprived samples

library(pheatmap)
## Warning: package 'pheatmap' was built under R version 4.2.2
log2<-results$padj<.00000000000001
log2[is.na(log2)]<-FALSE
resSort2 <- results[order(log2,decreasing = FALSE),]
tg <- head(rownames(resSort2),25)
mat <- assay(dds[tg,])
mat <- mat - rowMeans(mat)
df <- as.data.frame(colData(dds)[,c("con","sample")])
pheatmap(mat, annotation_col=df)

This tree shows the hierarchical clustering of the samples

r1000<-rownames(resSort[1:1000,])
val<-plotCounts(dds, gene=x, intgroup = "sample",col=factor(c("Healthy","Deprived")),returnData=TRUE)[,1]
for (x in r1000[2:1000]){
  val<-cbind(val,plotCounts(dds, gene=x, intgroup = "sample",col=factor(c("Healthy","Deprived")),returnData=TRUE)[,1])
}
rownames(val)<-sample<-c("S1_H","S1_D","S2_H","S2_D","S3_H","S3_D","S4_H","S4_D","S5_H","S5_D","S6_H","S6_D")
dis1000<-dist(val,method="euclidean")
cl1000<-as.dendrogram(hclust(d=dis1000,method="complete"))
plot(cl1000)
